This paper focuses on analyzing clustering in Wireless Sensor Networks (WSN) using a complex systems science approach. The paper discusses the relationships between system parts that result in certain properties of the whole system, which is a characteristic of networked systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a complexity metric to explain how local interactions give rise to the global behavior of the network, which is a characteristic of complex systems. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the energy efficiency of WSNs, which is a characteristic of systems that require resource management. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible sub-categories.
